title: Determination of carbon and oxygen in GaAs by means of 3He - activation

x4freetext: Determination of carbon and oxygen in GaAs
by means of 3He - activation

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.18, p.281 (1987)

x4freetext: 30 minutes irraiation with 400 nanoampere beam
current.
Short and long counting times after the
irradation offered the possibility of evaluating all
activities products.
The subtraction of the activities produced by
irradiation of thick targets using projectiles of diffe
ent energies allows the calculation of the mean cross
sections for the region between these energies.
The reaction products were identified and counted using
high resolution gamma-ray
7 MV

x4freetext: Digitizing error
Because of the successive subtraction the
overall eror connected with the cross section ranges
from 10% to 20% depending on the individual product
nucleus and its gamma-ray intensity. Therefore the
errors given on figures represent only the statistical
errors.
